ENTRY            A0935   20260207   20260508   20260508       A132
SUBENT        A0935001   20260207   20260508   20260508       A132
BIB                 11         29
TITLE      Isovector soft dipole mode in 6Be.
AUTHOR     (A.S.Fomichev,V.Chudoba,I.A.Egorova,S.N.Ershov,
           M.S.Golovkov,A.V.Gorshkov,V.A.Gorshkov,L.V.Grigorenko,
           G.Kaminski,S.A.Krupko,I.G.Mukha,Yu.L.Parfenova,
           S.I.Sidorchuk,R.S.Slepnev,L.Standylo,S.V.Stepantsov,
           G.M.Ter-Akopian,R.Wolski,M.V.Zhukov)
INSTITUTE  (4ZZZDUB,2GERGSI,4RUSKUR,3POLIFJ,4RUSMOS,
           3POLIPJ,2SWDCTH)
           (3CZRCZR) Silesian University in Opava, Czech Republic
REFERENCE  (J,PL/B,708,6,2012)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,4ZZZDUB)the U-400M cyclotron of FLNR and
           the double achromatic magnetic separator ACCULINNA
METHOD     (EDE,TOF)
           (COINC) two protons and alpha particle coincidences
INC-SOURCE A 47 A*MeV 6Li beam was produced at the U-400M
           cyclotron. A graphite degrader installed in front
           of ACCULINNA reduced the beam energy to 32.5 A MeV.
DETECTOR   (TELES,SI,CSICR) The reaction products were detected by
           two identical annular telescopes. Each telescope
           consisted of two position-sensitive silicon detectors
           of 300 and 1000 um thickness, respectively, and an
           array of 16 trapezoidal CsI(Tl) crystals with PIN-diode
           readouts.
SAMPLE     The 6 mm thick target cell having 6 mum stainless-steel
           windows was filled with hydrogen at a pressure of 3 bar
           and cooled down to 35 K.
STATUS     The letter was sent to Dr.I.A.Egorova 26.03.2012
HISTORY    (20120326C) SB
           (20260207U) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              29
COMMON               1          3
